ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMER FOR AI-AUGMENTED USE

The CADRE Framework specifies the design and deployment of multi-agent AI
systems built on Anthropic Claude (Opus, Sonnet) and other frontier large
language models. Outputs produced by such agents may contain factual errors,
hallucinations, omissions, biased reasoning, or content that is otherwise
incorrect or unsuitable for the intended use.

Operators of CADRE-based deployments are solely responsible for:

  1. ESTABLISHING APPROPRIATE HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP (HITL) GATES for any agent
     action that affects external parties, makes decisions of legal or
     financial consequence, or operates in a Cynefin Complex or Chaotic
     domain. The HITL tier taxonomy in `governance/hitl-tier-taxonomy.md`
     is provided as guidance, not as a legal safe harbor.

  2. VALIDATING AGENT OUTPUTS for accuracy, source attribution, and
     compliance with applicable laws and regulations including but not
     limited to the EU AI Act, Colorado AI Act, NIST AI RMF, ISO 42001,
     and any sector-specific obligations (healthcare HIPAA, finance
     SR 11-7 / OCC 2011-12, hiring AEDT laws, biometric BIPA, etc.).

  3. MAINTAINING AUDIT TRAILS sufficient to demonstrate human oversight,
     decision provenance, and incident response capability.

  4. DISCLOSING AI INVOLVEMENT to end users and counterparties to the
     extent required by applicable law, contract, or professional ethics.

The case-law precedents documented in `governance/case-law-precedents.md`
(Air Canada Moffatt v. Air Canada 2024 BCCRT 149; iTutor Group EEOC
settlement 2023; Klarna AI deployment reversal 2025) make clear that
operator liability for agent output is not abstract — it has been
adjudicated, settled, and publicly reversed. This framework does not
transfer that liability away from the operator.

Use at your own risk and under qualified human supervision.
